race.comment: IMMORTAL BLISS (7) has been left with too much to do in both runs this time in work, flying late at Mt Barker last start to miss by 1.7L. He's since switched to the Morton stable and the inside draw here can see him sit closer in the run. Third-up now and can go to another level now. SIBERIAN SIREN (3) ended last campaign in hot form, winning two in-a-row before the break. She'll be fitter for a couple of trials coming into this and the booking of Parnham signals their intent. Can sit close to the speed and bring up the hat-trick on resumption. SONOFTHEBOSS (4) is another looking for a hat-trick, scoring by 0.7L at this track and trip last time out. Cooper's claim comes in handy and he's beginning to hit his straps. Can play a leading role. WUBIN GOLD (6) will find this a little easier than what she's been racing in and a better showing is on the cards. ELITEONE (10) can be thereabouts on resumption.
